    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
    <p>EngageWorx is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards to ensure we provide equal access to all users.</p>

    <h2>Standards</h2>
    <p>We aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA. These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and more user-friendly for everyone.</p>

    <h2>Measures We Take</h2>
    <p>EngageWorx takes the following measures to ensure accessibility:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Semantic HTML structure with appropriate heading hierarchy</li>
      <li>Keyboard navigable interface — all interactive elements are accessible without a mouse</li>
      <li>Sufficient colour contrast ratios between text and background elements</li>
      <li>Clear, descriptive labels for form inputs and interactive controls</li>
      <li>Responsive design that adapts to different screen sizes and zoom levels</li>
      <li>Text alternatives for non-text content where applicable</li>
      <li>Focus indicators visible on all interactive elements</li>
      <li>Consistent navigation and predictable page structure</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Voice & Telephony Accessibility</h2>
    <p>Our voice IVR system is designed with accessibility in mind:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>DTMF keypad input as an alternative to speech recognition</li>
      <li>Clear, paced audio prompts using professional text-to-speech voices</li>
      <li>Voicemail transcription providing text alternatives to audio messages</li>
      <li>Repeat and timeout options for callers who need more time</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
    <p>While we strive for full accessibility, we acknowledge the following current limitations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Some complex dashboard visualisations (charts, heatmaps) may not be fully accessible to screen readers. We are working to provide text-based alternatives.</li>
      <li>The visual flow builder uses drag-and-drop interactions that may be difficult for keyboard-only users. An alternative configuration method is planned.</li>
      <li>Some third-party integrations may have their own accessibility limitations outside our direct control.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of EngageWorx. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:</p>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:accessibility@engwx.com">accessibility@engwx.com</a><br>
    Web: <a href="https://www.engwx.com">www.engwx.com</a></p>
    <p>We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days and to implement reasonable changes within 30 days where possible.</p>

    <h2>Enforcement</h2>
    <p>If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility concern, you may contact the Equality Advisory Support Service (EASS) at <a href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com">www.equalityadvisoryservice.com</a> or the Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) at <a href="https://www.equalityhumanrights.com">www.equalityhumanrights.com</a>.</p>
